snippet.textDisplay: If I wasn't alive to see Kobe with my own eyes, I might not believe this man was real. He's almost like a myth. I would never believe there was a person that went through the extreme lengths that Kobe did to be excellent at not only basketball, but literally everything that he pursued in life. The discipline, commitment, seeking of knowledge, eye for detail, along with his supreme confidence, charisma and passion for learning everything; from basketball and all it's intricacies, to multiple languages, to business, to writing novels, to poetry, to film-making, the list goes on. There was and never will be another like Kobe. People say a great person is a "1 in a million" or even a billion, and think that it's a huge compliment. Kobe was even rarer than that. I'll miss you forever Kobe. Now you can rest. Mamba forever ❤️
